Take an intimate look inside the minds of swimming's highest achievers with one of the world's best swim coaches, Brett Hawke.

As a swimmer, Brett swam in two Olympic Finals (2000, 2004) of the 50 Free. He never did quite break 22 seconds (22.07) but he did take a 100 Free out in 22.5 to his feet once. In college, he swam for Auburn University under legend David Marsh. He won the 50 Free at 1997 NCAA's in 19.19. 

After his pro swimming career, he became an Assistant Coach at Auburn University. At the 2008 Olympics in Beijing, he guided Cesar Cielo to victory in the Men's 50 Freestyle. Cesar's gold medal swim was the first in Brazil's history. In 2009, after the sudden passing of Richard Quick, Brett led an inspired team of Tigers through an emotionally charged NCAA's. 

Most recently, Brett helped guide Bruno Fratus to a Bronze medal in the Men's 50 Free at the Tokyo Olympics.

Iron Culture was started by Eric Helms and Omar Isuf as a means of exploring the world of physical culture and attempting to distill a unified philosophy of lifting and to help listeners find greater meaning from the iron. The lifting community has become fractured over the last ~70 years and this Podcast will attempt to explore the fundamental threads that unite these different tribes. The Podcast focuses on dispensing practical, useful information to the listener, bouncing from history, to philosophy, to contemporary lifting culture issues, to science. This can range from teaching the audience about lifting, programming, nutrition, supplements/PEDs and the history of lifting culture. The format includes casual conversations between the two hosts on a variety of topics, discussions with a panel of experts and interviews with authoritative figures in the lifting community.

The Tubthumping Podcast: Where The Most Inspiring Comeback Stories Live.
Ideas, discussions, and interviews with men and women on how to achieve a more fulfilling, successful life, when feelings of frustration, failure, overwhelm, and being stuck become your focus.
I know firsthand how this feels, having watched my 20 plus year career and life savings go up in smoke when I was fired from the company, I co-founded a decade earlier. After being stuck for years I started a personal development journey spanning years and thousands of hours of teachings from some good and not so good teachers. Over time I was able to disregard what didn't work and take only the best, most effective tools and assembled them into a streamlined process which helped me start getting results. I got myself back in shape, dropped 50lbs., back on a business track, out of debit, aligned spiritually, and reconnected with my family on a much deeper level. My Goal: I want you to feel as good as I do!
